Description. Head (
Fig. 4
): Structure: 1.22–1.31 times as high as long. Frons posteriorly 1.10–1.14 times as wide as long, anteriorly, at lunule level, 0.8 –1.0 times as wide as long. Face straight. Carina rounded at about dorsal 0.8 , ventral 0.2 flattened; carina protrusion about 0.9 times as long as parafacial at narrowest level. Eye 1.50–1.77 times as high as long, with sparse, short, whitish setulae. Gena 0.36–0.41 times as high as eye. Fronto-orbital plate at antenna insertion level 0.64–0.87 times as long as gena height. Pedicel 0.52–0.68 times as long as high at apex and 0.46–0.65 times as long as 1 st flagellomere; first flagellomere 1.20–1.26 times as long as high. Color and vestiture: Ocellar triangle black. Vertex orange medially, blackish laterally, gray microtrichose. Occiput mainly orange to brown, irregularly infuscate, gray microtrichose. Frons yellowish posteromedially, orange-brown anteriorly and laterally. Orbit beige, white microtrichose. Gena anteriorly beige and white microtrichose, posteriorly dark brown and slightly white microtrichose; postgena brown, gray microtrichose. Face, including carina, mostly pale orange to light brown except ventrally infuscate, inconspicuously white microtrichose; antennal groove brown to black, shiny medially, white microtrichose laterally; margin of subcranial cavity brown. Scape and pedicel orange, slightly white microtrichose; 1 st flagellomere orange, apically infuscate, slightly white microtrichose; arista orange to brown. Clypeus yellow, slightly gray microtrichose. Palp yellow to orange; proboscis dark brown. Chaetotaxy: Medial vertical seta 1.12–1.27 times as long as lateral vertical seta; ocellar and postocellar setae each 0.5–0.7 times as long as medial vertical seta; posterior orbital seta 1.3–1.5 times as long as anterior orbital seta and 0.5–0.7 times as long as medial vertical seta. Frons densely setulose, setulae 0.2–0.4 times as long as posterior orbital seta. Labium with long mixed black and yellow setulae. Gena with long black setulae and 1 seta. Vibrissal angle, postgena and occiput long setulose.

Wing (
Fig. 19
): Pattern: Mixed brown and yellow peripheral striped type pattern present; BB fully brown; SBB extending from costa to middle of cell dm basally; PB extending from costa over pterostigma except base, merging with SBB in cell r 2 + 3 , narrowed abruptly at crossvein R-M; SAB merges with AB in cells r 1 and r 2 + 3 ; cell r 4 + 5 brown peripherally, medially hyaline; brown band present over crossvein DM-Cu and apical half of vein Cu 1 . Yellow areas: Between BB and SBB, between SBB and PB and predominantly between PB and AB except anterior half (of area) nearly hyaline. Venation: Veins yellow to orange in hyaline areas, brown within dark bands. Cell r 4 + 5 0.93–0.97 times as wide at apex as at widest point. Crossvein R-M aligned slightly basal to apex of R 1 . Vein Cu 2 curved, cell bcu without posteroapical lobe. Calypteres white. Halter base brown, stem and knob whitish-yellow to orange. Wing length 4.60–8.60 mm .

Male terminalia: Epandrium (Fig. 7 ) 1.0– 1.1 times as high as wide, rounded in posterior view; medial surstylus fully fused with epandrium, bearing numerous prensisetae; lateral surstylus articulated to epandrium, bare and apically rounded. Phallus (
Fig. 10
) laterally on both sides with setulae as long as phallus width; medially at basal 0.33 bare and at distal 0.66 with setulae as long as phallus width. Glans membranous and setulose, except tip bare.

Female terminalia: Aculeus 5.2–6.1 times as long as wide. Cercal unit (
Fig. 13
) oval, with well pronounced, long lateral groove. Sensilla: BV apical to BD. Pair of large campaniform sensilla present distal to BV. 3 spermathecae, wrinkled, about 4.5 times as long as wide at widest place (Fig. 16 ) present.
